HEADWORD: Teleosaur
<hw>Te`le*o*saur"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of fossil suarians belonging to
Teleosaurus and allied genera. These reptiles are related to the
crocodiles, but have biconcave vertebrae.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

